includedActivitiesStart: The activity starts with warping and sizing of cotton yarn.
includedActivitiesEnd: This process ends with conversion of cotton yarn at weaving plant to 1 kg of woven fabric.
generalComment: Inventory refers to the weaving of 1 kg  yarn into textile, The activity begins with sizing and warping of yarn and ends with the woven fabric. It includes electricity use for warping, weaving and air conditioning. The yarn itself is not included. Data collected for a fabric of 236 grams per square meter (gsm) with a yarn of 20Tex (Nm50). Compared to the range of data available in literature (2-20 kWh/kg), the electricity use (3.1kWh/kg) is in the lower range. Data collected from mostly vertically integrated mills on a global level.
